      "body" : "half a day I have been looking for this. Worked for me with antlr4. Thanks!"
    }, {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 2451938,
        "reputation" : 20723,
        "user_id" : 2137996,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "accept_rate" : 77,
        "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/dYdyn.jpg?s=256",
        "display_name" : "Alex Reinking",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2137996/alex-reinking"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 2,
      "creation_date" : 1552423533,
      "post_id" : 35947085,
      "comment_id" : 97002318,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "For ANTLR &gt;=4.5.3 (maybe earlier, too), as long as my grammar was located in <code>src&#47;main&#47;antlr4&#47;&lt;path-to-package&gt;&#47;</code>, then it would appear in <code>target&#47;generated-sources&#47;antlr4&#47;&lt;path-to-package&gt;</code>. IntelliJ automatically marked the correct directory as a sources root and no package prefix was necessary. I suspect this fix is needed when people place their grammars directly in <code>src&#47;main&#47;antlr4</code>, which is often recommended for some reason."
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1291135,
      "reputation" : 3219,
      "user_id" : 2587343,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/52874e9b4f06834f233ea323925fd305?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Vlastimil Ovč&#225;č&#237;k",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2587343/vlastimil-ov%c4%8d%c3%a1%c4%8d%c3%adk"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 23,
    "last_activity_date" : 1457719871,
    "last_edit_date" : 1592644375,
    "creation_date" : 1457719871,
    "answer_id" : 35947085,
    "question_id" : 5170620,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<h3>The fix</h3>\n<p>Go to <em>Project Structure</em> - <em>Modules</em> - <em>Source Folders</em> and find the <code>target/generated-sources/antlr4/com/mycompany</code> - click <em>Edit properties</em> and set <em>Package prefix</em> to <code>com.mycompany</code>.</p>\n<p>This is exactly the reason why we can set <em>Package prefix</em> on source dirs.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><em>Different but related problem <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/35946928/2587343\">here</a></em></p>\n"
  }, {
